wave1_kofi.content:
BONDING is live.

I shipped an open-source chemistry game on my son's 10th birthday. I'm an autistic engineer; late diagnosis at 39. When the family-court window changed, I built BONDING — a multiplayer molecular builder where every atom placed is a timestamped engagement log.

{{c.bonding.testBaseline.tests}} automated tests across {{c.bonding.testBaseline.suites}} suites. Works offline. Runs on the Android tablets the kids already use. No accounts. No ads. No data collection.

Play: {{c.bonding.publicUrl}}

P31 Labs is a Georgia nonprofit (EIN {{c.organization.ein}}; 501(c)(3) determination pending). The code is MIT and will outlive any single deploy. Support keeps me building.

